This paper deals with the construction and decoding of polar codes for channels with memory, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional kernels in the polar code construction, which is related to signal processing (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the decoding algorithm, which is related to computer networks (cs.NI).
